------------------ GIT COMMANDS BELOW : ------------------ 

------------------ To create (init) & push into a git repository ------------------
> git init
> git add .
> git commit -m "commit-msg"
> git remote add origin <git repository path>
> git push origin master

If you face buffer error while pushing, use below command : 
> git config --global http.version HTTP/1.1

And then revert it back to : 
> git config --global http.version HTTP/2

If you face user issue while using git add . command (in another system)
> git config --global --add safe.directory <system repository path with forward slashes>

